## Problem

BLite provides no way to integrate with external key management systems (Azure Key Vault, AWS KMS, HSM). Without this, teams cannot adopt BLite encryption in production environments that require centralized key management and key rotation policies.

## Appetite

**Small batch — ~2 days**

## Solution

**New file:** `src/BLite.Core/Encryption/IKeyProvider.cs`
```csharp
public interface IKeyProvider
{
    ValueTask<ReadOnlyMemory<byte>> GetKeyAsync(string databaseName, CancellationToken ct);
    ValueTask NotifyKeyRotationAsync(string databaseName, CancellationToken ct);
}
```

**Add `EncryptionOptions` to `BLiteEngineOptions`:**
```csharp
public sealed class EncryptionOptions
{
    public string? Passphrase { get; init; }          // Option 1: direct passphrase (simple apps)
    public IKeyProvider? KeyProvider { get; init; }   // Option 2: external KMS (production)
    public EncryptionAlgorithm Algorithm { get; init; } = EncryptionAlgorithm.AesGcm256;
    public KdfAlgorithm Kdf { get; init; } = KdfAlgorithm.Pbkdf2;
    public int KdfIterations { get; init; } = 100_000;
}
```

On engine open: resolve key via `IKeyProvider.GetKeyAsync` (or derive from passphrase), initialize `EncryptionCoordinator`, assign providers to all storage components. When encryption is not configured, all providers default to `NullCryptoProvider` — zero overhead.

## Rabbit Holes

- The `Passphrase` option is convenient for development but unsuitable for production — document this clearly.
- `IKeyProvider` is called once at open time, not on every page read/write.

## No-gos

- BLite does not implement its own KMS or key storage.
- Key rotation is a separate issue.

## Problem

`DocumentCollection.Watch()` with `capturePayload=true` broadcasts the full BSON document to all observers. If the document contains PII (email, SSN, health data), this exposes sensitive fields in plaintext to every CDC subscriber — violating GDPR Art. 5(1)(c) (data minimisation principle).

## Appetite

**Small batch — ~1 day**

## Solution

**Extend `WatchOptions`:**
```csharp
public sealed class WatchOptions
{
    public bool CapturePayload { get; init; } = false;

    /// <summary>
    /// If CapturePayload = true, these fields are stripped from the payload before notification.
    /// </summary>
    public IReadOnlyList<string> ExcludeFields { get; init; } = [];

    /// <summary>
    /// If set, only these fields are included in the payload (allowlist takes precedence).
    /// </summary>
    public IReadOnlyList<string>? IncludeOnlyFields { get; init; }
}
```

**In `ChangeStreamDispatcher` / payload capture path:**
- If `ExcludeFields` is non-empty: remove those fields from the cloned BSON document before dispatching
- If `IncludeOnlyFields` is set: project only those fields (allowlist model takes precedence over ExcludeFields)
- If `CapturePayload = false`: no change (existing behaviour, no payload cloning)

## Rabbit Holes

- Field masking must operate on a **clone** of the document — do not modify the in-memory page buffer.
- `ExcludeFields` and `IncludeOnlyFields` apply only when `CapturePayload = true`; if `CapturePayload = false`, these options have no effect.

## No-gos

- Field masking in query results (not CDC) is a separate concern.
- Encrypted field storage is out of scope for this issue.

## Problem

GDPR Art. 30 requires data controllers to maintain records of processing activities. Applications using BLite have no programmatic way to inspect what collections exist, what fields they contain, whether encryption is enabled, what retention policies are configured, or which fields are marked as personal data. This makes compliance audits laborious and error-prone.

## Appetite

**Small batch — ~2 days**

## Solution

**New API on `BLiteEngine`:**
```csharp
DatabaseInspectionReport InspectDatabase();
```

```csharp
public sealed class DatabaseInspectionReport
{
    public string DatabasePath { get; init; }
    public bool IsEncrypted { get; init; }
    public bool IsAuditEnabled { get; init; }
    public bool IsMultiFileMode { get; init; }
    public IReadOnlyList<CollectionInfo> Collections { get; init; }
}

public sealed class CollectionInfo
{
    public string Name { get; init; }
    public long DocumentCount { get; init; }
    public long StorageSizeBytes { get; init; }
    public IReadOnlyList<IndexInfo> Indexes { get; init; }
    public IReadOnlyList<string> PersonalDataFields { get; init; }  // from [PersonalData] attributes
    public RetentionPolicyInfo? RetentionPolicy { get; init; }
}
```

**Implementation:**
- Reads from existing `StorageEngine` metadata (catalog, collection registry)
- `PersonalDataFields` populated from source-generated metadata (requires `[PersonalData]` attribute issue); falls back to empty list if source generation is not used
- `DocumentCount` read from the catalog (maintained counter), not from a full scan

## Rabbit Holes

- `StorageSizeBytes` in multi-file mode includes all associated files (collection files + index files).
- This is a read-only inspection API — it does not modify any collection configuration.

## No-gos

- The inspection report does not constitute a GDPR Art. 30 record of processing activities by itself — it is input data that the application must incorporate into its own compliance documentation.
